<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Opening the Controls panel</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  At the top of the dashboard, locate the <strong>Controls</strong> panel. If it's collapsed, click on it to expand:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-19">
  <li>
    Click the <strong>Controls</strong> bar at the top of the dashboard
  </li>
  <li>
    You'll see two dropdown filters:
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-font-size-16">
      <li><strong>Service Area</strong> - currently showing "All"</li>
      <li><strong>Region</strong> - currently showing "All"</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-6">Filtering by Service Area</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Let's filter to see just one service area:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-19">
  <li>
    Click the <strong>Service Area</strong> dropdown (currently set to "All")
  </li>
  <li>
    You'll see a list of 9 service areas with checkboxes:
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-font-size-16">
      <li>Benefits</li>
      <li>Council Tax</li>
      <li>Customer Services</li>
      <li>Environmental Health</li>
      <li>Highways</li>
      <li>Housing</li>
      <li>Parking</li>
      <li>Planning Applications</li>
      <li>Waste Collection</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    Click "Select all" to uncheck all options
  </li>
  <li>
    Select only <strong>"Housing"</strong>
  </li>
  <li>
    Click outside the dropdown or press Escape to close it
  </li>
  <li>
    Watch all widgets update instantly to show only Housing data
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="ndx-wow-moment">
  <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">The wow moment: Real-time filtering</h4>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    When you selected Housing, QuickSight instantly filtered the data:
  </p>
  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-font-size-16">
    <li><strong>Total Cases:</strong> Changed from 267,334 → 29,760 (Housing only)</li>
    <li><strong>Bar charts:</strong> Now show only Housing as a single bar</li>
    <li><strong>Table:</strong> Now shows Housing broken down by 8 regions</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    <strong>Technical detail:</strong> SPICE (Super-fast, Parallel, In-memory Calculation Engine) stores data
    in compressed columnar format. The filter was applied and all visuals updated in milliseconds - faster than
    refreshing an Excel spreadsheet.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-6">Understanding Housing performance by region</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  With Housing selected, look at the Service Performance Breakdown table:
</p>

<table class="govuk-table">
  <caption class="govuk-table__caption govuk-table__caption--s">Housing performance by region</caption>
  <thead class="govuk-table__head">
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Region</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Cases</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Resolved</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Satisfaction</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody class="govuk-table__body">
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">West Midlands</th>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">4,253</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">3,583</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell"><strong>4.15</strong></td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">North East</th>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">4,244</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">3,665</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell"><strong>4.22</strong></td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">London</th>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">3,798</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">3,222</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell"><strong style="color: #00703c;">4.38</strong> (highest)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">North West</th>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">3,601</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">3,150</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell"><strong style="color: #d4351c;">3.88</strong> (lowest)</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body">
    <strong>Insight:</strong> Housing satisfaction varies significantly by region. London (4.38) has the highest
    satisfaction while North West (3.88) has the lowest. This 0.5 point difference is significant - it could indicate
    different service delivery approaches, resource allocation, or housing stock conditions.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-6">Resetting filters</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  To see all data again:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-19">
  <li>
    Click the <strong>Reset</strong> button in the top-left corner (circular arrow icon)
  </li>
  <li>
    All filters return to "All" and dashboard shows full dataset (267,334 cases)
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Filtering by Region</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Now try filtering by geographic region:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-19">
  <li>
    Click the <strong>Region</strong> dropdown
  </li>
  <li>
    You'll see 8 regions:
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-font-size-16">
      <li>East Midlands</li>
      <li>London</li>
      <li>North East</li>
      <li>North West</li>
      <li>South East</li>
      <li>South West</li>
      <li>West Midlands</li>
      <li>Yorkshire</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    Select only <strong>"London"</strong>
  </li>
  <li>
    Dashboard now shows all 9 service areas, but only for London region
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body">
    <strong>Use case:</strong> Regional managers can view their region's performance across all services.
    London Housing Manager sees London data. Yorkshire Highways Manager sees Yorkshire highways data.
    Same dashboard, personalized view.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-6">Combining filters</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  You can apply both filters together:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-19">
  <li>
    Set <strong>Service Area</strong> to "Housing"
  </li>
  <li>
    Set <strong>Region</strong> to "London"
  </li>
  <li>
    Dashboard now shows only Housing cases in London (3,798 cases, 4.38 satisfaction)
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="ndx-comparison govuk-!-margin-top-4">
  <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Before/After comparison: Service analysis</h4>

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
      <h5 class="govuk-heading-s">Before QuickSight (Manual Excel)</h5>
      <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-16">
        <li>Manager emails analyst: "How is Housing performing in London?"</li>
        <li>Analyst opens Excel, applies filters to raw data (10 min)</li>
        <li>Analyst creates pivot table and charts (20 min)</li>
        <li>Analyst formats and emails back (10 min)</li>
        <li>Manager asks follow-up: "Compare to North West?" (repeat process)</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body-s"><strong>Total time:</strong> 40+ minutes per question</p>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
      <h5 class="govuk-heading-s">After QuickSight (Self-Service)</h5>
      <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-!-font-size-16">
        <li>Manager opens QuickSight dashboard (5 seconds)</li>
        <li>Selects "Housing" from Service Area dropdown (2 seconds)</li>
        <li>Selects "London" from Region dropdown (2 seconds)</li>
        <li>Sees answer instantly - 3,798 cases, 4.38 satisfaction</li>
        <li>Changes Region to "North West" for comparison (2 seconds)</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body-s"><strong>Total time:</strong> 15 seconds per question</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-6">Reflection: Questions you answered</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  In this 3-minute step, you answered these questions through interactive exploration:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-font-size-19">
  <li>"How many Housing cases are we handling?" → 29,760 (filtered from 267K total)</li>
  <li>"Which region has highest Housing satisfaction?" → London (4.38)</li>
  <li>"Which region has lowest Housing satisfaction?" → North West (3.88)</li>
